Cheat sheet...

#check versions of things
$ ruby -v
$ rails -v
$ rvm list
$ rvm gemset list

#toggle between gemsets
$ rvm gemset use global
$ rvm gemset use default
$ rvm gemset use learn-rails

#include hidden files in list:
$ ls -1pa

There are three forms of the git add command:
• git add foo.txt adds a file named foo.txt
• git add . adds all new files and changed files, except deleted files
• git add -A adds everything, including deletions

View project history
$ git log
$ git log --oneline

